      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The report is ready. Here\u2019s a quick summary of the findings:\n\n- **Baseline 2022 U.S. emissions:** 5,200\u202fMtCO\u2082e.\n- **Policy levers:** 10\u202fMha afforestation (\u2248150\u202fMtCO\u2082e net uptake by 2050) and a $50\u202ft\u207b\u00b9CO\u2082e carbon tax starting 2025.\n- **Resulting emissions 2050:** 2,500\u202fMtCO\u2082e, a 52\u202f% reduction from the baseline.\n- **Projected climate impacts for the U.S. by 2050:**\n  \u2022 Mean temperature increase of **+2.0\u202f\u00b0C** (global +1.8\u202f\u00b0C).\n  \u2022 Precipitation increase of **+5\u202f%**.\n  \u2022 Sea\u2011level rise of **+0.12\u202fm**.\n- **State\u2011level temperature change:** Visualized in the choropleth map.\n- **Emission trajectory:** Shown in the interactive time\u2011series chart.\n\nYou can view the full report and visual assets here:\n- Report (PDF): https://climavision.io/reports/afforestation_carbon_tax_USA.pdf\n- Temperature map: https://climavision.io/viz/temperature_map_USA.png\n- Emissions time\u2011series: https://climavision.io/viz/emissions_timeseries_USA.html\n\nLet me know if you\u2019d like to explore alternative policy settings, drill down into a specific state, or export the data in another format.",
